From ad027445c2daccc4e3caf5a8f7c0d8917def4da7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 20:50:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] hdc daemon: cap USB bulk writes to stable size for hybris
 devices

Companion to the existing OnUSBRead 61KB cap for the Volla X23
native-boot (hybris) target. The Halium Android vendor 5.10 kernel's
FunctionFS gadget cannot satisfy a single bulk-IN write larger than
~61KB either, so `hdc file recv` (device -> host) of any file > ~60KB
hangs the session on the very first CMD_FILE_DATA packet -- the
daemon's write(bulkIn, ~49KB) never completes, the host's
libusb_bulk_transfer never returns, and any later `hdc shell` call
wedges the daemon's shell channel until the device reboots. The same
hang also broke `mcp__ohos-hdc__screenshot` / `dump_layout`, which
recv the captured artifact internally.

Cap each write() call in HdcDaemonUSB::SendUSBIOSync at
GetUsbffsBulkSizeStable() (61KB) inside the existing offset-resume
loop; bigger hdc packets still go through across multiple writes. No
host-side hdc change is required.

Verified end-to-end: recv of 18B / 64KB / 1MB / 5MB / 20MB all land
with matching md5sums, 10 sequential 1MB recvs in a row, interleaved
send+recv stable, `hdc shell` survives, and the MCP screenshot tool
captures the X23 lockscreen.

Change-Id: I0c31495d9c917e29e419a035a84da46befaf6531
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/daemon/daemon_usb.cpp | 15 ++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/daemon/daemon_usb.cpp b/src/daemon/daemon_usb.cpp
index 6c2cfe14..25852b23 100644
--- a/src/daemon/daemon_usb.cpp
+++ b/src/daemon/daemon_usb.cpp
@@ -307,9 +307,22 @@ int HdcDaemonUSB::SendUSBIOSync(HSession hSession, HUSB hMainUSB, const uint8_t
     int childRet = 0;
     int ret = ERR_IO_FAIL;
     int offset = 0;
+    // Volla X23 / hybris native boot: symmetric to the OnUSBRead 61KB cap.
+    // The Halium (Android vendor) 5.10 kernel's FunctionFS gadget cannot
+    // satisfy a single bulk-IN write larger than ~61KB either -- hdc file
+    // recv (device -> host) of any file > ~60KB hangs the session because
+    // the daemon's write(bulkIn, ~48KB) on the very first CMD_FILE_DATA
+    // packet never completes. Cap each write() at the 61KB "stable" size
+    // so every write is satisfiable; bigger hdc packets still go through
+    // across multiple writes via the existing offset-resume loop below.
+    const int usbWriteCap = Base::GetUsbffsBulkSizeStable();
     StartTraceScope("HdcDaemonUSB::SendUSBIOSync");
     while (modRunning && isAlive && !hSession->isDead) {
-        childRet = write(bulkIn, const_cast<uint8_t *>(data) + offset, length - offset);
+        int wantWrite = length - offset;
+        if (wantWrite > usbWriteCap) {
+            wantWrite = usbWriteCap;
+        }
+        childRet = write(bulkIn, const_cast<uint8_t *>(data) + offset, wantWrite);
         if (childRet <= 0) {
             int err = errno;
             if (err == EINTR) {
